<subSubSection pageId="84" pageNumber="85" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="84.[151,1436,401,595]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,443,469]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body fusiform; scapular setae (
<emphasis box="[719,743,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">sc</emphasis>
) and tubercles on rear shield margin, directed posteriorly; legs with usual segmentation and setae, empodium entire; coxae I and coxae II each with 3 setae; opisthosoma with 3 ridges, first three dorsal annuli narrower than others.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="84.[151,1436,401,595]" box="[208,751,569,595]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
